    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-05-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-05-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="152" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d152">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. F. W. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Yeaman</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 14.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-05-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 18, 1866</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of the 23d instant, No. 13,
                            has been received, and that part of it relating to the articles, now in
                            your custody, which formerly belonged to the iron-clad Stoerkodder, or
                            Stonewall, has been referred to the Secretary of the Navy, who, in a
                            letter just received at this department, suggests that the articles
                            referred to be shipped to the United States for the purpose of being
                            placed on board that vessel. You are consequently instructed to lose no
                            time in giving effect to the suggestion of the Secretary of the
                            Navy.</p>
                <p>The information communicated in your despatch concerning political
                            affairs in Denmark has been read with much interest.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F. W. SEWARD, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">George H. Yeaman,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
